## Exercise 13: View Available Signals

Display all signals supported by Linux.

```bash
kill -l
```

Identify:

* SIGTERM (15)
* SIGKILL (9)
* SIGSTOP (19)
* SIGCONT (18)

---

## Exercise 14: Using pkill

1. Start multiple sleep processes.

```bash
sleep 500 &
sleep 500 &
sleep 500 &
```

2. Verify.

```bash
ps -ef | grep sleep
```

3. Kill all sleep processes.

```bash
pkill sleep
```

4. Verify again.

```bash
ps -ef | grep sleep
```

---

## Exercise 15: Process Priority and Nice Value

1. Display process priorities.

```bash
top
```

Observe:

* PR = Priority
* NI = Nice Value

---

2. Start a process with default nice value.

```bash
sleep 300 &
```

3. Start a process with lower priority.

```bash
nice -n 10 sleep 300 &
```

4. Check priorities.

```bash
ps -el
```

Observe the PRI and NI columns.

---

## Exercise 16: Change Nice Value of a Running Process

1. Start a process.

```bash
sleep 300 &
```

2. Find PID.

```bash
ps -ef | grep sleep
```

3. Change nice value.

```bash
renice 5 -p PID
```

4. Verify.

```bash
ps -el
```

